---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ChapterStyles from '../components/ChapterStyles.astro';

const lessons = [
  { icon: 'Σ', label: 'hackathon → $1.5M', body: "Won a month-long GenAI hackathon against 50+ developers from Tiger Analytics, McKinsey, and TCS Research. The team's end-to-end AI product recommendation system on Azure converted straight into a $1.5M CPG contract." },
  { icon: '◐', label: 'Data Companion', body: 'Built an enterprise-grade Text2SQL system on AWS Bedrock + Snowflake + Claude 3.5 Sonnet. 90% query accuracy. Showcased at AWS Tech Summit 2024 in Las Vegas. Generated $1M in revenue off rapid-deploy capability.' },
  { icon: '◈', label: 'Visualize', body: "Architected a platform where users generate analytics dashboards in natural language. Dashboard creation: days → minutes. Also shipped an industry-first auto-generation of Power BI dashboards with LLM-derived DAX queries." },
  { icon: '⇄', label: 'multi-agent RAG', body: 'Led the creation of a multi-agent GenAI recommendation engine on Azure — RAG, dynamic knowledge graphs, semantic search, enterprise-grade reliability. The closest I got to PortoAI\'s architectural pattern before starting PranaAlpha Labs.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Sigmoid — Venkateshwar Reddy Jambula">
  <ChapterStyles />
  <article class="ch">
    <header class="ch-header">
      <a href="/" class="ch-back">&larr; home</a>
      <div class="ch-eyebrow">June 2024 – May 2025 &middot; Principal Data Scientist &middot; GenAI</div>
      <h1>Sigmoid.</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="ch-opener">
      <p class="ch-lede">
        A year at Sigmoid doing enterprise GenAI &mdash; the chapter
        where I got to stress-test my reliability instincts at real
        client scale, demo&rsquo;d in <em>Las Vegas</em>, and quietly
        assembled the instincts for what PranaAlpha Labs would become.
      </p>
      <figure class="feature-photo">
        <img src="/images/sigmoid/conference.jpg" alt="Tech conference keynote" loading="eager" />
        <figcaption>data companion &middot; demo&rsquo;d at AWS Tech Summit, Las Vegas 2024</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section">
      <h2>A year in four shipped systems.</h2>
      <div class="lesson-grid">
        {lessons.map((l) => (
          <article class="lesson">
            <div class="l-icon">{l.icon}</div>
            <div class="l-label">{l.label}</div>
            <p>{l.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section">
      <h2>Enterprise GenAI, at scale.</h2>
      <p>
        Sigmoid was where I applied everything I&rsquo;d learnt &mdash;
        from industrial ML at Caterpillar, supply-chain RL at Continental,
        voice at Samsung, markets solo &mdash; to a new generation of
        clients with real budgets and real urgency. I led an
        innovative proof-of-concept on using GenAI to automate traditional
        ML workflows: model selection, feature engineering, hyperparameter
        tuning, all via natural language.
      </p>
      <p>
        The year compressed a lot. A prestigious hackathon against
        McKinsey teams turned into a $1.5M contract with a CPG client.
        <em>Data Companion</em>, a Text2SQL system we built on AWS
        Bedrock + Snowflake + Claude 3.5 Sonnet, reached 90% query
        accuracy through query optimization and contextual enrichment.
        AWS flew the system to <strong>Las Vegas</strong> as a Tech
        Summit showcase. Rapid deployment alone drove $1M in revenue.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section">
      <h2>The stack of a year.</h2>
      <div class="gallery g-2">
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/sigmoid/vegas.jpg" alt="Las Vegas" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>AWS Tech Summit &middot; Las Vegas &middot; 2024</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/sigmoid/datacenter.jpg" alt="Data center" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>enterprise scale &middot; where the demos had to hold</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p class="photo-credit">Photos: Wikimedia Commons (CC).</p>
    </section>

    <section class="ch-section ch-close">
      <blockquote>
        <p>
          By mid-2025 I knew two things. First: enterprise GenAI was
          going to be a crowded, competitive, highly-funded space. Second:
          the hard problem &mdash; the one nobody was solving &mdash;
          wasn&rsquo;t &ldquo;can an agent complete a task.&rdquo; It
          was &ldquo;can an agent stay trustworthy across days, not
          minutes.&rdquo; I left Sigmoid to work on exactly that
          question. PranaAlpha Labs was founded two weeks later.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <footer class="ch-foot"><a href="/" class="ch-back-cta">&larr; back to the story</a></footer>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
